<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 16 at 8:20AM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
northeastern Tazewell, central Bland and southwestern Mercer Counties
through 845 AM EDT...
At 819 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Gary, or 9 miles north of Tazewell, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Bluefield...
Bland...
Princeton...
Tazewell...
Rocky Gap...
Bastian...
and Burkes Garden.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
